  "notes": "Burmese Myanmar script abugida. 4-tone system (creaky low, level/plain, high falling, checked glottal). Inherent vowel is /a/. The script has 33 base consonant letters; many Sanskrit-derived letters have merged in pronunciation. သ = dental fricative /θ/. Tone and vowel quality interact with final consonants. This spec gives base consonant correspondences; full G2P requires syllable structure analysis.",
